<TITLE> Deep-sea port building starts late next year </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 15 (bdnews24.com)The government will start a three-phase construction of a deep-sea port in the Bay of Bengal by the end of the next year, the shipping minister said on Wednesday. Afsarul Amin told reporters after a meeting at the Secretariat that the first phase of the work in the Sonadia Island in Cox's Bazar at a cost of Tk 13,000 crore was expected to end by 2015. The port would be operational after the first phase of work, the minister said. The second segment will start between 2016 and 2017, Amin said. Together with the second and the final stage, the work will cost Tk 60,000 crore and end in 2055. Wednesday's meeting discussed the study report of the consultant group on technical and economic feasibility of the port. The report may be sent to the Cabinet Committee on Economic Relations Division, the minister said and added that the committee would send it to the cabinet after finalisation. The deep-sea port is touted to boost up export-import trade and increase growth by 1.5 percent. bd
